News24 Correspondent(File, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Two KZN police officers have been injured after a shootout with robbers in KwaDukuza on Saturday morning, IPSS Medical Rescue said."A number of armed people went in and robbed [lending company]&hellip; Supreme Finance," said the rescue company&rsquo;s Dylan Meyrick."When they came out, they were surprised by the police and a shootout occurred."He said the police officers were not seriously injured.A manhunt was currently underway with a police helicopter circling the area around King Shaka Street where the robbery occurred.He said it was alleged that the robbers got away with hundreds of thousands of rands. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.